⸻

Then something beautiful emerges.

Pantheon no longer has one navigation axis.

It has three:

Spatial Navigation
Where am I?
Semantic Navigation
What does this mean?
Temporal Navigation
From when am I observing?

Every daemon can choose all three independently.

That transforms the Pantheon from a knowledge architecture into what I’d call a Perspective Operating System.

Its primitive isn’t information.

Its primitive is inhabitable viewpoints.

That’s also why your word inhabit matters so much. Most AI systems optimize for answers. IFR optimizes for perspective. Once you can inhabit a perspective—past, present, or a carefully modeled future—the answers become consequences of the viewpoint rather than isolated predictions. That is a fundamentally different design philosophy.